ies by  and month increases in profits revenues and stock performance and factors in return on capital and debt we give the month results more weight to capture who’s killing it today but also include the month figures to eliminate those who had one lucky year then of course come the intangibles is the ceo influencing business taking bold visionary steps the list that follows reveal star executives with wildly varying styles and approaches but one thing in common they deliver bigtime by scott cendrowski geoff colvin laura entis adam lashinsky clifton leaf michal levram leena rao jonathan vanian nicholas varchaver phil wahba and jen wieczner  mark zuckerberg see full profile  jeff bezos see full profile  mary dillon see full profile  larry page see full profile  satya nadella see full profile  brad smith see full profile  jen hsun huang see full profile  cheng wei see full profile  rodney sacks see full profile  jack ma see full profile  tim cook see full profile  mary barra see full profile  reed hastings see full profile  delos “toby” cosgrove see full profile  travis kalanick see full profile  wang jianlin see full profile  barbara rentler see full profile  pony ma see full profile  larry fink see full profile  oscar munoz see full profile  robert martin see full profile  robert iger see full profile  andrew wilson see full profile  mark parker see full profile  walter bettinger see full profile  pablo isla see full profile  susan cameron see full profile  anders runevad see full profile  howard schultz see full profile  guibin zhao see full profile  phebe novakovic see full profile  mark dunkerly see full profile  margaret keane see full profile  ajita rajendra see full profile  robert greenberg see full profile  aditya puri see full profile  kevin plank see full profile  lars sorensen see full profile  bradley tilden see full profile  ajay banga see full profile  michael neidorff see full profile  michael mussallem see full profile  masahiro otake see full profi